      "side": 0,
      "message": "It\u0027s partially code clean-up.  Cleaning up this code will help us complete the implementation of SkColorSpaceXformCanvas which we need for Android (O release) and Chrome - this canvas needs to inspect all the SkPaints and do color xforms on them, incuding the paints that are hidden in draw loopers.\n\nTechnically, we don\u0027t need this for Android O because SkPaints are implicitly sRGB and the destination of the SkColorSpaceXformCanvas will be sRGB.  So the paint transform is no-op - it\u0027s ok if we miss some paints.\n\nThis does matter for Chrome though.\n\nWhen do we branch?  I\u0027d rather not wait too long.",
